<div id="content"><div id="cpad"><h2>Annual Publication Lists</h2>
<h3>In-Press and Accepted Publications</h3>
<p>The papers listed below have been accepted for publication.</p>

<div id="hl_block">&nbsp;</div>

<script>document.getElementById("hl_block").innerHTML='<p id="hl_on">+ <a href="javascript:toggleGA(1);">Highlight</a> GISS authors</p><p id="hl_off">+ <a href="javascript:toggleGA(0);">Unhighlight</a> GISS authors</p>'</script>


<p><span class="gissauthor">Cesana, G.V.</span>, <span class="gissauthor">O. Pierpaoli</span>, <span class="gissauthor">M. Ottaviani</span>, <span class="gissauthor">L. Vu</span>, and <span class="gissauthor">Z. Jin</span>, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/ce08200c.html">The correlation between Arctic sea ice, cloud phase and radiation using A-train satellites</a>. <cite>Atmos. Chem. Phys.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p>Crosbie, E., L. Ziemba, M. Shook, T. Shingler, J. Hair, A. Sorooshian, R. Ferrare, <span class="gissauthor">B. Cairns</span>, Y. Choi, J. DiGangi, G. Diskin, C. Hostetler, S. Kirschler, R.H. Moore, D. Painemal, C. Robinson, S. Seaman, K. Thornhill, C. Voigt, and E. Winstead, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/cr04100o.html">Measurement report: Cloud and environmental properties associated with aggregated shallow marine cumulus and cumulus congestus</a>. <cite>Atmos. Chem. Phys.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p><span class="gissauthor">DeLessio, M.A.</span>, <span class="gissauthor">K. Tsigaridis</span>, <span class="gissauthor">S.E. Bauer</span>, <span class="gissauthor">J. Chowdhary</span>, and G.L. Schuster, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/de06900s.html">Modeling atmospheric brown carbon in the GISS ModelE Earth system model</a>. <cite>Atmos. Chem. Phys.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p><span class="gissauthor">Field, R.D.</span>, M. Luo, <span class="gissauthor">S.E. Bauer</span>, <span class="gissauthor">J.E. Hickman</span>, <span class="gissauthor">G.S. Elsaesser</span>, <span class="gissauthor">K. Mezuman</span>, <span class="gissauthor">M. van Lier-Walqui</span>, <span class="gissauthor">K. Tsigaridis</span>, and <span class="gissauthor">J. Wu</span>, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/fi09300n.html">Estimating the impact of a 2017 smoke plume on surface climate over northern Canada with a climate model, satellite retrievals, and weather forecasts</a>. <cite>J. Geophys. Res. Atmos.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p><span class="gissauthor">Gornitz, V.</span>, 2023: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/go00700s.html">The nature of Quaternary climate change</a>. In <cite>Encyclopedia of Quaternary Science, 3rd Edition</cite>, Elsevier, in press, doi:10.1016/B978-0-323-99931-1.00099-4.</p>
<p>Luo, M., H.M. Worden, <span class="gissauthor">R.D. Field</span>, <span class="gissauthor">K. Tsigaridis</span>, and <span class="gissauthor">G.S. Elsaesser</span>, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/lu09100t.html">TROPESS CrIS CO single pixel vertical profiles: Intercomparisons with MOPITT and model comparisons for 2020 US Western wildfires</a>. <cite>Atmos. Meas. Tech.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p>M&uuml;lmenst&auml;dt, J., E. Gryspeerdt, S. Dipu, J. Quaas, <span class="gissauthor">A.S. Ackerman</span>, <span class="gissauthor">A.M. Fridlind</span>, <span class="gissauthor">F. Tornow</span>, <span class="gissauthor">S.E. Bauer</span>, A. Gettelman, Y. Ming, Y. Zheng, P.-L. Ma, H. Wang, K. Zhang, M.W. Christensen, A.C. Varble, L.R. Leung, X. Liu, D. Neubauer, D.G. Partridge, P. Stier, and T. Takemura, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/mu04200y.html">General circulation models simulate negative liquid water path-droplet number correlations, but anthropogenic aerosols still increase simulated liquid water path</a>. <cite>Atmos. Chem. Phys.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p><span class="gissauthor">Obiso, V.</span>, M. Gon&ccedil;alves Ageitos, C. P&eacute;rez Garc&iacute;a-Pando, G.L. Schuster, <span class="gissauthor">S.E. Bauer</span>, C. Di Biagio, P. Formenti, <span class="gissauthor">J.P. Perlwitz</span>, <span class="gissauthor">K. Tsigaridis</span>, and <span class="gissauthor">R.L. Miller</span>, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/ob06000g.html">Observationally constrained regional variations of shortwave absorption by iron oxides emphasize the cooling effect of dust</a>. <cite>Atmos. Chem. Phys.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p>Ren, F., J. Lin, C. Xu, J.A. Adeniran, J. Wang, R.V. Martin, A. van Donkelaar, M. Hammer, L. Horowitz, S.T. Turnock, N. Oshima, J. Zhang, <span class="gissauthor">S. Bauer</span>, <span class="gissauthor">K. Tsigaridis</span>, &Oslash;. Seland, P. Nabat, D. Neubauer, G. Strand, T. van Noije, P. Le Sager, and T. Takemura, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/re08100s.html">Evaluation of CMIP6 model simulations of PM<sub>2.5</sub> and its components over China</a>. <cite>Geosci. Model Dev.</cite>, accepted.</p>
<p><span class="gissauthor">Roach, L.A.</span>, M.M. Smith, A. Herman, and <span class="gissauthor">D. Ringeisen</span>, 2024: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/ro04910m.html">Physics of the seasonal sea ice zone</a>. <cite>Annu. Rev. Mar. Sci.</cite>, accepted.</p>
